1
00:00:03,900 --> 00:00:06,900
War. War never changes.

2
00:00:08,101 --> 00:00:11,000
The Romans waged war
to gather slaves and wealth.

3
00:00:11,401 --> 00:00:15,900
Spain built an empire from
its lust for gold and territory.

4
00:00:16,001 --> 00:00:21,000
Hitler shaped a battered Germany
into an economic superpower.

5
00:00:21,001 --> 00:00:24,000
But war never changes.

6
00:00:24,001 --> 00:00:29,500
In the 21st century, war was still waged
over the resources that could be acquired.

7
00:00:31,001 --> 00:00:36,000
Only this time, the spoils of
war were also its weapons.

8
00:00:36,501 --> 00:00:38,000
Petroleum and uranium.

9
00:00:38,901 --> 00:00:43,000
For these resources, China would invade
Alaska, the U.S. would annex Canada,

10
00:00:43,901 --> 00:00:45,608
and the European
Commonwealth would dissolve

11
00:00:46,820 --> 00:00:48,000
into quarreling,
bickering nation-states

12
00:00:48,801 --> 00:00:52,000
bent on controlling the last
remaining resources on Earth.

13
00:00:53,001 --> 00:00:56,000
In 2077, the storm of
World War had come again.

14
00:00:56,501 --> 00:01:02,000
In two brief hours, most of the
planet was reduced to cinders.

15
00:01:02,001 --> 00:01:08,000
And from the ashes of nuclear devastation,
a new civilization would struggle to arise.

16
00:01:09,001 --> 00:01:14,000
A few were able to reach the relative
safety of the large underground vaults.

17
00:01:14,901 --> 00:01:19,000
Your family was part of that
group that entered Vault 13.

18
00:01:20,001 --> 00:01:24,000
Imprisoned safely behind the large
vault door, under a mountain of stone,

19
00:01:24,001 --> 00:01:29,000
a generation has lived without
knowledge of the outside world.

20
00:01:30,601 --> 00:01:34,600
Life in the vault is about to change.

